      • toDb

        @Nonnull
public com.mongodb.DBObject toDb(@Nonnull
                                          T entity,
                                          @Nonnull
                                          List<MapperError> errors)
        Converts an entity to a DBObject. Errors are collected into the errors parameters, they will not stop the conversion. The most specific mapper is search for, so a mapper can be used to convert an instance of a sub-class.

        Note that the corresponding mapperRegistry should be initialized first.

        Parameters:
        entity - Entity to convert to a database object.
        errors - Collection to collect errors in.
        Returns:
        Converted database object, will never be null.

      • toDb

        public void toDb(@Nonnull
                 T entity,
                 @Nonnull
                 com.mongodb.DBObject dbObject,
                 @Nonnull
                 List<MapperError> errors)
        Converts an entity into a given dbObject. Mapped fields will be copied onto the dbObject. Pre-existing values will not be removed from the dbObject.

        Note that the corresponding mapperRegistry should be initialized first.

        Parameters:
        entity - Entity to copy data from. May not be null.
        dbObject - Database object to copy data into. May not be null.
        errors - List to collect errors in.
